publications.name: Traffic Congestion Index Estimation for Road Using Fuzzy Logic
publications.description: Traffic congestion occurs when traffic comes to a complete stop or slows to less than its normal speed. Nobody wants to find themselves in this situation. It is stressful, causing those unfortunate enough to be caught up in it to arrive at their destinations later than planned and lengthening travel time. It is, nevertheless, a fact of life in and between urban regions all throughout the world. Rising traffic congestion is unavoidable in one of the significant and increasing metropolitan regions around the world. To depict the true traffic situation, the proposed study has used the factors like giving the imprecision of traffic records, the user's assessment of the road's degree of service given, and fluctuation in sample data is required. A fuzzy inference-based technique has been used to meet these needs. The aim is to find a novel accuracy for the following problem statement.

publications.name: Data Science System of Predicting and Detecting the Chikungunya Virus using Ensemble Techniques
publications.description: The ailment known as chikungunya fever is brought on by a virus that mosquitoes disseminate. Due to the infection's excruciating joint and muscular discomfort, the term translates to ‚Äúbends you up‚Äù or ‚Äústooped walk.‚Äù The abrupt onset of a high temperature, headache, exhaustion, rash, nausea, and red eyes are other symptoms. Chikungunya symptoms frequently show up 2 to 7 days after being bitten by an infected mosquito. There isn't a vaccination yet. Additionally, there is no cure for the illness. However, fatalities or major complications with chikungunya are uncommon. Many people recover in a matter of weeks. However, some people experience joint and muscular discomfort that can linger for months or even years after they have been exposed to the virus. After one to two weeks, a lot of people are free of further problems. Others, though, can experience joint and muscular discomfort for years. This kind of arthritis is known as chronic chikungunya. At least 40persons who contract the virus are affected. Chikungunya is seldom fatal. But for certain people, the infection can lead to serious issues. Older persons, those with chronic illnesses like diabetes or high blood pressure, small children, and pregnant women who could pass the virus to their unborn children are at increased risk. Serious issues with the eyes, heart, and nerves can be complications. Once-infected individuals are likely to be resistant to subsequent infections. The main aim of the authors is to use the ensemble technqiue to find a novel approach and to compare the ensemble techniques

publications.name: Prediction of Bankruptcy of a company using machine learning techniques
publications.description: Bankruptcy prediction is an important modern technique because it helps not only the policy makers but the investors and all concerned people so they can take all necessary steps to prevent or to reduce the after effects of bankruptcy. Companies take a large quantity of loan and when they become bankrupt the entire system of the bank is shattered as it is really tough to get the given money bank. Hence, it is must needed to develop a system that could predict it the company‚Äôs bankruptcy and stop the loan. It is observed that the newer machine learning prediction model is outperforming the models of past thirteen years, using relatively small data but this data is still very big and balanced. Some of the machine learning models or techniques are Random Forest, XGBoost, Vector Machines. The main motive of the paper aims to compare the machine learning models which are support vector machine, random forest and XGBoost and give which one performs the best amongst them and give a novel accuracy.
